          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1651572359419-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> [all]</span><strong> </strong>the <strong>wholegrain</strong> <strong>mustard</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining wholegrain mustard for another recipe!</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and whisk together – this is your <strong>mustard vinaigrette</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>truffle oil </strong>in a separate bowl – this is your<strong> truffle mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1651572377220-x200.jpg",
